WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:00.034 --> 00:00:03.037
<i>Epic theme playing...</i>

2
00:00:03.120 --> 00:00:05.915
[♪ ♪]

3
00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:13.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

4
00:00:40.366 --> 00:00:44.161
[♪ ♪]

5
00:01:43.387 --> 00:01:45.055
(Solemn music playing)

6
00:01:47.725 --> 00:01:49.435
(Birds chirping)

7
00:01:52.855 --> 00:01:54.899
(Wind blowing)

8
00:02:09.580 --> 00:02:12.625
[♪ ♪]

9
00:02:41.445 --> 00:02:43.906
(Indistinct chatter)

10
00:02:46.283 --> 00:02:48.118
(Cookware clinking)

11
00:03:02.049 --> 00:03:03.884
[♪ ♪]

12
00:03:03.968 --> 00:03:05.241
Queen Alicent:
<i>You're sure?</i>

13
00:03:05.330 --> 00:03:06.915
(Sobs)

14
00:03:09.598 --> 00:03:11.058
Talya:
With his own eyes. Your Grace.

15
00:03:19.650 --> 00:03:21.277
(Sniffles) Uh...

16
00:03:23.237 --> 00:03:25.364
Stay here.
Tell. tell no one.

17
00:03:26.532 --> 00:03:29.201
Help me dress.

18
00:03:29.285 --> 00:03:31.078
[♪ ♪]

19
00:03:43.883 --> 00:03:45.467
Who knows?

20
00:03:48.929 --> 00:03:50.598
My handmaiden. Talya.

21
00:03:51.515 --> 00:03:54.560
<i>Some of the servants.</i>

22
00:03:58.522 --> 00:04:00.524
<i>I saw him last night...</i>

23
00:04:01.525 --> 00:04:04.570
before he...

24
00:04:07.698 --> 00:04:09.909
He told me he wished
for Aegon to be king.

25
00:04:18.751 --> 00:04:20.377
It is the truth.

26
00:04:21.295 --> 00:04:23.297
Uttered with his own lips.

27
00:04:23.380 --> 00:04:26.967
His last words to me and I
was the only one to hear it.

28
00:04:28.302 --> 00:04:29.637
And now he's dead.

29
00:04:31.722 --> 00:04:34.767
[♪ ♪]

30
00:04:59.917 --> 00:05:02.878
(Sighs) What is it that could
not have waited an hour?

31
00:05:02.962 --> 00:05:04.588
Was Dorne invaded?

32
00:05:08.133 --> 00:05:09.885
The King is dead.

33
00:05:19.937 --> 00:05:22.398
We grieve
for Viserys the Peaceful...

34
00:05:23.732 --> 00:05:25.275
our sovereign...

35
00:05:27.569 --> 00:05:28.654
our friend.

36
00:05:32.700 --> 00:05:34.326
But he has left us a gift.

37
00:05:37.955 --> 00:05:42.042
With his last breath. he impressed
upon the Queen his final wish:

38
00:05:42.126 --> 00:05:45.587
That his son. Aegon...

39
00:05:45.671 --> 00:05:49.717
should succeed him
as Lord of the Seven Kingdoms.

40
00:05:51.969 --> 00:05:54.888
(Thunder rumbles)

41
00:05:58.851 --> 00:06:01.103
Then we may proceed now
with the full assurance

42
00:06:01.186 --> 00:06:04.023
of his blessing
on our long-laid plans.

43
00:06:04.106 --> 00:06:06.025
Otto High tower: Yes.
There is much to be done.

44
00:06:06.108 --> 00:06:07.651
as we've previously discussed.

45
00:06:07.735 --> 00:06:09.778
Now. there are two
among the captains

46
00:06:09.862 --> 00:06:12.489
of the City Watch that
remain loyal to Daemon.

47
00:06:12.573 --> 00:06:15.012
Let us replace them.
Lord Lannister.

48
00:06:15.097 --> 00:06:16.702
Tyland Lannister:
The Treasury is well in hand.

49
00:06:16.785 --> 00:06:18.746
The gold will be divided
for safekeeping.

50
00:06:18.831 --> 00:06:19.963
Otto: Let ravens
be sent to our allies.

51
00:06:20.047 --> 00:06:22.249
River run and High garden.

52
00:06:22.332 --> 00:06:23.751
Am I to understand that
members of the small council

53
00:06:23.834 --> 00:06:27.546
have been planning secretly
to install my son without me?

54
00:06:27.629 --> 00:06:31.175
My Queen. there was no need to
sully you with darkling schemes.

55
00:06:31.258 --> 00:06:33.010
Lyman Beesbury:
I will not have this.

56
00:06:33.093 --> 00:06:35.137
To hear that you are plotting

57
00:06:35.220 --> 00:06:38.307
to replace the King's
chosen heir

58
00:06:38.390 --> 00:06:39.475
- with an imposter!
- Tyland: His firstborn son

59
00:06:39.558 --> 00:06:42.603
- is hardly an imposter.
- Lyman: Hundreds of lords

60
00:06:42.686 --> 00:06:45.355
and landed knights
swore fealty to the Princess.

61
00:06:45.439 --> 00:06:47.274
Tyland: That was some 20
years ago. Most of them now dead.

62
00:06:47.357 --> 00:06:48.692
Jasper Wylde:
You heard the Lord Hand.

63
00:06:48.776 --> 00:06:51.070
Plot or no.
the King changed his mind.

64
00:06:51.862 --> 00:06:54.573
I am six-and-seventy years old.

65
00:06:54.656 --> 00:06:59.119
I have known Viserys longer
than any who sit at this table.

66
00:06:59.203 --> 00:07:00.662
And I will not believe
that he said this

67
00:07:00.746 --> 00:07:06.877
on his deathbed. alone. with only
the. the boy's mother as a witness.

68
00:07:07.878 --> 00:07:09.922
This is seizure!

69
00:07:10.005 --> 00:07:12.424
It is theft!
It is treason!

70
00:07:12.508 --> 00:07:16.303
- At the least. it is...
- Mind your tongue. Lyman.

71
00:07:16.386 --> 00:07:18.847
The King was
well last night...

72
00:07:18.931 --> 00:07:20.557
by all accounts.

73
00:07:21.850 --> 00:07:26.939
Which of you here can swear
that he died of his own accord?

74
00:07:27.022 --> 00:07:30.734
Which of us are you accusing
of regicide. Lord Beesbury?

75
00:07:30.818 --> 00:07:32.528
Lyman:
Whether it was one of you.

76
00:07:32.611 --> 00:07:35.155
or all of you. I care not.

77
00:07:35.239 --> 00:07:36.240
- I will have no part...
- Sit down!

78
00:07:36.323 --> 00:07:39.243
- Lyman: Ahh!
- Alicent: Ser Criston.

79
00:07:50.963 --> 00:07:54.383
Throw down your sword and
remove your cloak. Ser Criston.

80
00:07:56.343 --> 00:07:59.012
I am your Lord Commander.
Ser Criston.

81
00:07:59.096 --> 00:08:00.597
Cast down your sword.

82
00:08:00.681 --> 00:08:04.184
I will not suffer insults
to Her Grace the Queen.

83
00:08:04.268 --> 00:08:07.354
There was no insult to me. Ser
Criston. Y... Put aside your blade.

84
00:08:15.654 --> 00:08:18.448
- Has it come to this?
- Lord Commander. enough.

85
00:08:22.119 --> 00:08:26.707
- Let us have Lord Beesbury removed.
- Otto: No.

86
00:08:26.790 --> 00:08:30.043
The door remains shut
until we finish our business.

87
00:08:46.977 --> 00:08:48.604
Storm's End is of concern.

88
00:08:48.687 --> 00:08:52.065
We may not assume
the loyalty of Lord Borros.

89
00:08:52.149 --> 00:08:54.860
But he has four daughters.
all of them unmarried.

90
00:08:54.943 --> 00:08:58.030
- The right proposal...
- What of Rhaenyra?

91
00:08:58.113 --> 00:09:01.909
The former heir cannot. of
course. be allowed to remain free

92
00:09:01.992 --> 00:09:05.746
and draw support to her claim.

93
00:09:05.829 --> 00:09:08.290
- Alicent: You mean to imprison her.
- Otto: She and her family

94
00:09:08.373 --> 00:09:09.625
will be given the opportunity

95
00:09:09.708 --> 00:09:13.086
to publicly swear obeisance
to the new King.

96
00:09:13.170 --> 00:09:15.088
She will never bend the knee.

97
00:09:15.172 --> 00:09:17.925
Nor will Daemon. which you know.

98
00:09:23.347 --> 00:09:24.932
You plan to kill them.

99
00:09:29.269 --> 00:09:31.647
And all here accede to this.

100
00:09:31.730 --> 00:09:34.066
Grand Maester Orwyle: Your
father is correct. Your Grace.

101
00:09:34.149 --> 00:09:37.778
A living challenger invites
battle and bloodshed.

102
00:09:37.861 --> 00:09:39.780
It is unsavory. yes.

103
00:09:39.863 --> 00:09:43.283
But a sacrifice we must make
to secure Aegon's succession.

104
00:09:43.367 --> 00:09:46.286
And then there is
Daemon to consider.

105
00:09:46.370 --> 00:09:48.914
- The King wouldn't wish for any unsavory...
- But the King did not wish

106
00:09:48.997 --> 00:09:51.792
for the murder of his daughter!

107
00:09:51.875 --> 00:09:53.794
He loved her.
I will not have you deny this.

108
00:09:53.877 --> 00:09:55.837
- And yet...
- One more word. and I will have you removed

109
00:09:55.921 --> 00:09:57.881
from this chamber
and sent to the Wall!

110
00:10:08.559 --> 00:10:11.353
What do you suggest.
Your Grace?

111
00:10:13.981 --> 00:10:15.691
- (Sighs)
- Otto: Time is of the essence.

112
00:10:26.660 --> 00:10:28.537
Lord Commander We sterling...

113
00:10:29.454 --> 00:10:31.999
take your knights
to Dragons tone.

114
00:10:32.082 --> 00:10:33.917
Be quick and be clean.

115
00:10:48.265 --> 00:10:49.785
I am Lord Commander
of the Kings guard.

116
00:10:53.645 --> 00:10:56.690
I recognize no authority
but the King's.

117
00:10:57.774 --> 00:10:59.609
And until there is one...

118
00:11:02.070 --> 00:11:03.905
I have no place here.

119
00:11:05.282 --> 00:11:08.327
[♪ ♪]

120
00:11:15.792 --> 00:11:16.710
Princess Helaena:
<i>It is our fate. I think.</i>

121
00:11:16.793 --> 00:11:19.713
<i>to crave always what
is given to another.</i>

122
00:11:19.796 --> 00:11:24.092
If one possesses a thing.
the other will take it away.

123
00:11:24.176 --> 00:11:26.261
Yes. Princess.

124
00:11:26.762 --> 00:11:28.347
(Door opens)

125
00:11:29.181 --> 00:11:30.557
Where is Aegon?

126
00:11:33.852 --> 00:11:35.562
N-Not here.

127
00:11:35.645 --> 00:11:36.772
He's not in his rooms.

128
00:11:44.571 --> 00:11:45.822
Father.

129
00:11:48.492 --> 00:11:49.576
(Children babbling)

130
00:11:55.207 --> 00:11:56.833
What's happened?

131
00:12:03.048 --> 00:12:06.843
[♪ ♪]

132
00:12:11.890 --> 00:12:15.143
- Your father...
- There is a beast beneath the boards.

133
00:12:15.227 --> 00:12:17.312
Oh. my dearest love.

134
00:12:22.401 --> 00:12:24.778
(Footsteps approach)

135
00:12:38.583 --> 00:12:40.127
Ser Erryk.

136
00:12:43.797 --> 00:12:44.589
Where's the Prince?

137
00:12:44.673 --> 00:12:47.384
Forgive me. Lord Hand.
I do not know.

138
00:12:47.467 --> 00:12:50.804
But you're sworn
to protect him.

139
00:12:50.887 --> 00:12:52.639
He exploits his authority
to order me away.

140
00:12:52.722 --> 00:12:53.922
and then he evades me.
my Lord.

141
00:12:58.728 --> 00:13:01.940
I believe he may have
left the Keep secretly.

142
00:13:02.023 --> 00:13:03.692
gone into the city.

143
00:13:03.775 --> 00:13:05.861
- Find him.
- (footsteps approach)

144
00:13:10.115 --> 00:13:12.659
Take no one else
but your brother.

145
00:13:12.742 --> 00:13:14.453
And remove
your white cloaks.

146
00:13:14.536 --> 00:13:16.296
None can know who you are
or what you seek...

147
00:13:17.289 --> 00:13:19.303
including the Queen.

148
00:13:19.490 --> 00:13:21.409
My Lord.

149
00:13:22.491 --> 00:13:25.172
Bring him to me. and me alone.
Ser Erryk.

150
00:13:31.803 --> 00:13:32.888
(Door locking)

151
00:13:35.348 --> 00:13:38.727
(Tense music playing)

152
00:13:43.773 --> 00:13:46.818
What is the meaning of this?

153
00:13:52.866 --> 00:13:54.910
[♪ ♪]

154
00:14:06.254 --> 00:14:08.006
Guard. Guard!

155
00:14:08.089 --> 00:14:09.883
[♪ ♪]

156
00:14:22.479 --> 00:14:25.440
Prince Aegon's not to be found
within the castle walls. Your Grace.

157
00:14:25.524 --> 00:14:27.764
Your father has sent Ser
Erryk into the city to find him.

158
00:14:30.445 --> 00:14:33.198
Ser Erryk knows Aegon.
He has the advantage.

159
00:14:40.288 --> 00:14:43.041
I trust again to you.
Ser Criston.

160
00:14:43.124 --> 00:14:44.918
and to your loyalty.

161
00:14:45.001 --> 00:14:48.588
Aegon must be found. and
he must be brought to me.

162
00:14:48.672 --> 00:14:50.632
The very fate of the Seven
Kingdoms depends on it.

163
00:14:51.925 --> 00:14:55.804
Everything you feel for me...
as your Queen.

164
00:14:57.347 --> 00:15:00.600
I will not fail you.

165
00:15:00.684 --> 00:15:01.685
Prince Aemond:
I'll come with you.

166
00:15:01.768 --> 00:15:04.980
That would not be
my desire. Aemond.

167
00:15:05.063 --> 00:15:09.943
- If anything has happened...
- Cole needs me. Mother.

168
00:15:10.026 --> 00:15:13.280
Ser Erryk isn't the only one
who knows Aegon's doings.

169
00:15:17.993 --> 00:15:19.786
[♪ ♪]

170
00:15:23.039 --> 00:15:24.624
(Door opens)

171
00:15:25.375 --> 00:15:27.502
(Door closes)

172
00:15:27.586 --> 00:15:29.170
(Bells tolling)

173
00:15:30.380 --> 00:15:32.465
(Dog barking)

174
00:15:39.598 --> 00:15:41.224
Aemond: <i>Aegon brought
me to the Street of Silk</i>

175
00:15:41.308 --> 00:15:42.851
on my thirteenth name day.

176
00:15:42.934 --> 00:15:46.146
It was his duty
as my brother. he said.

177
00:15:46.229 --> 00:15:49.441
to ensure I was
as educated as he was.

178
00:15:53.445 --> 00:15:55.822
At least that's what
I understood him to mean.

179
00:15:59.242 --> 00:16:01.077
I don't follow.

180
00:16:01.161 --> 00:16:02.829
He said.
“Time to get it wet.”

181
00:16:02.912 --> 00:16:05.915
Every woman is
an image of the Mother.

182
00:16:05.999 --> 00:16:07.334
to be spoken of
with reverence.

183
00:16:07.417 --> 00:16:10.253
(Bell ringing)

184
00:16:16.384 --> 00:16:17.636
<i>Sometime last night. we...</i>

185
00:16:17.719 --> 00:16:21.139
<i>misplaced
our drinking companion.</i>

186
00:16:21.222 --> 00:16:24.684
<i>Knowing that he has been. in the
past. a patron of your fine establishment.</i>

187
00:16:24.768 --> 00:16:26.908
<i>we thought to inquire here
as to his whereabouts.</i>

188
00:16:27.181 --> 00:16:28.515
And describe him.

189
00:16:29.648 --> 00:16:31.775
That is a delicate matter.

190
00:16:32.710 --> 00:16:34.405
(Softly)
You see. the man we seek

191
00:16:34.523 --> 00:16:35.862
is the young Prince Aegon.

192
00:16:35.945 --> 00:16:39.449
I may trust. I hope.
in the discretion of your trade.

193
00:16:39.532 --> 00:16:40.700
(Chuckles)

194
00:16:40.784 --> 00:16:42.869
The Prince is not here.

195
00:16:42.952 --> 00:16:47.666
Has he been here?
Earlier. perhaps?

196
00:16:47.749 --> 00:16:51.795
- Quite a bit earlier. Years ago. in fact.
- But more recently?

197
00:16:53.588 --> 00:16:56.800
He does not frequent
the Street of Silk.

198
00:16:56.883 --> 00:16:59.052
His tastes are known to be...

199
00:16:59.636 --> 00:17:02.347
less discriminating.

200
00:17:03.139 --> 00:17:04.182
Meaning what?

201
00:17:05.767 --> 00:17:10.772
I wish you luck. good Ser.
And my best to your friend.

202
00:17:16.528 --> 00:17:18.905
How you've grown.

203
00:17:21.992 --> 00:17:25.036
Aemond: Hm.

204
00:17:26.621 --> 00:17:28.748
Otto:
Viserys amended his wishes.

205
00:17:28.832 --> 00:17:30.792
It's as simple as that.

206
00:17:32.127 --> 00:17:35.046
You once swore
your banners to Rhaenyra.

207
00:17:35.130 --> 00:17:37.090
You must now

208
00:17:37.173 --> 00:17:39.843
pledge them
to the future king.

209
00:17:46.683 --> 00:17:51.938
I must confer first
with my house on this matter.

210
00:17:52.021 --> 00:17:55.066
You'll not leave this room
without declaring your intention.

211
00:18:04.701 --> 00:18:07.829
I am no oath breaker.

212
00:18:10.540 --> 00:18:12.375
I will not bend the knee.

213
00:18:19.632 --> 00:18:22.010
Otto: Anyone else?

214
00:18:34.063 --> 00:18:38.068
House Fell... keeps its
sworn oath to the Princess.

215
00:18:41.488 --> 00:18:43.573
Very well.

216
00:18:47.202 --> 00:18:49.996
[♪ ♪]

217
00:19:03.593 --> 00:19:04.803
Long live the King.

218
00:19:04.886 --> 00:19:07.722
All:
Long live the King.

219
00:19:15.480 --> 00:19:17.941
[♪ ♪]

220
00:19:18.024 --> 00:19:20.652
(Ambient street noise)

221
00:19:28.201 --> 00:19:30.036
(Indistinct chatter)

222
00:19:38.795 --> 00:19:41.673
Criston Cole: <i>It seems you were
mistaken as to Aegon's habits.</i>

223
00:19:41.756 --> 00:19:44.384
Aemond: <i>He could be in
the hands of mercenaries.</i>

224
00:19:44.467 --> 00:19:45.927
<i>on a ship to Yi Ti.</i>

225
00:19:46.886 --> 00:19:49.013
<i>He could be dead.</i>

226
00:19:49.097 --> 00:19:51.378
Let us hope. for your mother's
sake. that is not the case.

227
00:19:57.522 --> 00:19:59.357
(Distant yelling)

228
00:20:07.323 --> 00:20:08.867
- Man 1: Let's have a look.
- (groaning)

229
00:20:08.950 --> 00:20:11.452
- Go on.
- Man 2: Come here. Come here!

230
00:20:11.536 --> 00:20:14.330
- Get in there. you little...
- (crowd cheering)

231
00:20:20.545 --> 00:20:21.754
Yeah!

232
00:20:23.047 --> 00:20:26.050
Come on!

233
00:20:26.342 --> 00:20:27.802
(Child screams)

234
00:20:27.886 --> 00:20:29.304
(Crowd exclaiming)

235
00:20:31.014 --> 00:20:34.100
(Grunting) - Arryk
Cargyll: How old are they?

236
00:20:34.184 --> 00:20:37.729
Erryk Cargyll:
About 10 years. I should say.

237
00:20:37.812 --> 00:20:40.982
They have them grow
their nails and file the teeth.

238
00:20:41.065 --> 00:20:42.400
Makes them more formidable.

239
00:20:43.864 --> 00:20:47.655
- Come on!
- Prince Aegon spends many a night in this place.

240
00:20:47.739 --> 00:20:49.991
Do you see now what he is?

241
00:20:50.074 --> 00:20:51.367
<i>You've not seen everything.</i>

242
00:20:54.245 --> 00:20:55.830
(Crowd cheering)

243
00:21:00.001 --> 00:21:02.921
Aegon's?
One of many. I'd wager.

244
00:21:06.507 --> 00:21:09.302
[♪ ♪]

245
00:21:19.562 --> 00:21:22.690
Aemond: Here I am. trawling
the city. ever the good soldier

246
00:21:22.774 --> 00:21:26.277
in search of a wastrel who's never
taken half an interest in his birthright.

247
00:21:29.113 --> 00:21:31.950
'Tis I the younger brother who
studies history and philosophy.

248
00:21:32.033 --> 00:21:33.660
it is I who trains
with the sword.

249
00:21:33.743 --> 00:21:34.702
who rides the largest
dragon in the world.

250
00:21:34.786 --> 00:21:37.163
It is I who should be...

251
00:21:40.667 --> 00:21:43.628
I know what it is to toil for
what others are freely given.

252
00:21:43.711 --> 00:21:45.463
Mm.

253
00:21:47.966 --> 00:21:50.593
And we can't find him. Cole.

254
00:21:50.677 --> 00:21:53.680
You are a decent man
with no taste for depravity.

255
00:21:53.763 --> 00:21:55.682
His secrets are his own...

256
00:21:55.765 --> 00:21:57.058
and he's welcome to them.

257
00:21:57.141 --> 00:21:59.852
I'm next in line
to the throne.

258
00:21:59.936 --> 00:22:02.438
Should they come
looking for me.

259
00:22:02.522 --> 00:22:04.190
I intend to be found.

260
00:22:14.117 --> 00:22:17.161
Ser Arryk: <i>Something must
be done. Aegon is unfit to rule.</i>

261
00:22:17.245 --> 00:22:19.080
You tolerated the Prince's
proclivities for years.

262
00:22:19.163 --> 00:22:20.081
Because it was
my sworn duty. Arryk.

263
00:22:20.164 --> 00:22:22.041
It's for the Hand
to find wisdom.

264
00:22:22.125 --> 00:22:25.211
We swore an oath
of service until death.

265
00:22:25.294 --> 00:22:28.214
Jayne:
A moment of your time. m'lords.

266
00:22:28.297 --> 00:22:30.258
You'll find no buyers
for your wares here.

267
00:22:34.762 --> 00:22:37.807
I can take you to Prince Aegon.

268
00:22:38.141 --> 00:22:41.144
Rather. I am sent by one
who knows where he is.

269
00:22:41.227 --> 00:22:42.387
Who'll tell you. for a price.

270
00:22:44.856 --> 00:22:47.483
Deliver him. and we'll
consider your price.

271
00:22:47.567 --> 00:22:52.447
My mistress will not treat
with the servants of the Keep...

272
00:22:52.530 --> 00:22:55.283
exalted though they may be.

273
00:22:55.366 --> 00:22:57.702
She'll trust this to
the Hand of the King only.

274
00:22:57.785 --> 00:22:59.787
Impossible.

275
00:22:59.871 --> 00:23:03.791
I think he will wish to hear what
the White Worm can tell him.

276
00:23:03.875 --> 00:23:05.960
(Crowd cheering)

277
00:23:11.716 --> 00:23:14.552
(Bells tolling)

278
00:23:20.016 --> 00:23:21.768
Knight:
Halt! Hold the gate!

279
00:23:21.851 --> 00:23:23.728
(Horse neighs)

280
00:23:24.854 --> 00:23:26.105
Allun Caswell:
Let go of me!

281
00:23:26.189 --> 00:23:27.899
Larys Strong:
<i>He was fleeing from the gate.</i>

282
00:23:27.982 --> 00:23:28.775
Allun:
Do you know who I am?

283
00:23:28.858 --> 00:23:30.485
Larys:
<i>A warning for the Princess.</i>

284
00:23:30.568 --> 00:23:33.446
<i>I'd wager.</i>

285
00:23:33.529 --> 00:23:34.655
What say you?

286
00:23:36.032 --> 00:23:38.910
The Lord Confessor
presumes.

287
00:23:40.411 --> 00:23:42.914
I have no love
for the Princess.

288
00:23:42.997 --> 00:23:46.209
And where were you going then
with such urgency?

289
00:23:52.048 --> 00:23:54.175
Let the King's Justice take him.

290
00:23:58.513 --> 00:23:59.514
Allun: Let go of me!

291
00:23:59.597 --> 00:24:02.350
- No! This is not right!
- You did well. Lord Larys.

292
00:24:02.433 --> 00:24:05.871
- Allun: I will...
- Only my duty. my Lord Hand.

293
00:24:05.956 --> 00:24:07.177
Allun: (faintly)
Who do you think you are?

294
00:24:07.261 --> 00:24:09.471
You've spent many hours
with the Queen of late.

295
00:24:15.738 --> 00:24:21.035
There's no reason those hours
could not. in the end. benefit you.

296
00:24:22.912 --> 00:24:26.791
(Solemn music playing)

297
00:24:50.982 --> 00:24:54.777
[♪ ♪]

298
00:25:17.842 --> 00:25:19.427
(Sniffles)

299
00:25:39.822 --> 00:25:41.449
(Door opens)

300
00:25:50.708 --> 00:25:53.878
I will do you the considerable
courtesy of assuming

301
00:25:53.961 --> 00:25:55.880
there is a good reason
for the outrage

302
00:25:55.963 --> 00:25:57.882
of my treatment
here this morning.

303
00:25:59.008 --> 00:26:01.469
My sincerest regrets
for the lack of ceremony.

304
00:26:04.889 --> 00:26:06.224
The King.

305
00:26:11.354 --> 00:26:14.106
And you are
usurping the throne.

306
00:26:14.190 --> 00:26:16.108
It was my husband's
dying wish.

307
00:26:16.192 --> 00:26:17.109
- (Scoffs)
- Believe it or no.

308
00:26:17.193 --> 00:26:19.904
it is of no consequence.

309
00:26:19.987 --> 00:26:21.280
Aegon will be king.

310
00:26:24.867 --> 00:26:27.453
I came here
to ask your support.

311
00:26:27.536 --> 00:26:31.082
Well. I must credit you
for your boldness.

312
00:26:31.165 --> 00:26:33.167
House Velaryon
has long allied itself

313
00:26:33.251 --> 00:26:35.544
with the Princess Rhaenyra
and what has it gained you?

314
00:26:37.630 --> 00:26:40.841
Your daughter dead...
alone in Pentos.

315
00:26:41.926 --> 00:26:43.719
Your son cuckolded.

316
00:26:43.803 --> 00:26:46.055
Rhaenyra's heirs
are none of yours.

317
00:26:47.348 --> 00:26:52.311
It is your husband who grasps
so heedlessly for the throne.

318
00:26:52.395 --> 00:26:54.188
And even he
has abandoned you:

319
00:26:54.272 --> 00:26:56.899
Gone these six long years
to fight a desperate battle.

320
00:26:56.983 --> 00:27:00.069
returning grievously.
if not mortally. wounded.

321
00:27:00.152 --> 00:27:02.780
leaving the Lady of Driftmark
to chart her course alone.

322
00:27:05.574 --> 00:27:08.494
The word of my house
is not fickle.

323
00:27:10.621 --> 00:27:13.708
No. But. dear cousin...

324
00:27:15.543 --> 00:27:19.672
you more than any soul alive
understand what I say now.

325
00:27:19.755 --> 00:27:21.382
Princess Rhaenys.
I loved my husband.

326
00:27:21.465 --> 00:27:24.302
but I will speak
the truth we both know.

327
00:27:25.011 --> 00:27:26.762
You should've been queen.

328
00:27:29.348 --> 00:27:31.517
I little thought to hear
those words from you.

329
00:27:31.600 --> 00:27:34.343
The Iron Throne was yours
by blood and by temperament.

330
00:27:34.428 --> 00:27:37.148
Viserys would've lived
his days a country lord.

331
00:27:37.231 --> 00:27:39.150
content to hunt
and study his histories.

332
00:27:39.233 --> 00:27:40.568
but... here we are.

333
00:27:43.555 --> 00:27:44.572
We do not rule

334
00:27:44.655 --> 00:27:48.075
but we may guide
the men that do.

335
00:27:48.159 --> 00:27:49.869
Gently...

336
00:27:49.952 --> 00:27:52.246
away from violence
and sure destruction

337
00:27:52.330 --> 00:27:55.124
- and instead toward peace.
- Ugh.

338
00:27:55.207 --> 00:27:58.377
Is it in the name of peace
that you've imprisoned me?

339
00:27:58.461 --> 00:28:00.629
- And what of my dragon?
- If we are over matched.

340
00:28:00.713 --> 00:28:03.049
Rhaenyra will be tempted to
strike us. and war will ensue.

341
00:28:03.132 --> 00:28:04.884
(Sighs)

342
00:28:04.967 --> 00:28:08.220
Without your dragon. she
may be persuaded to negotiate.

343
00:28:09.722 --> 00:28:12.683
If it's Driftmark you want.
you shall have it

344
00:28:12.767 --> 00:28:17.188
for you and your granddaughters
to pass on as you see fit.

345
00:28:21.942 --> 00:28:23.652
You are wiser than
I believed you to be...

346
00:28:27.948 --> 00:28:30.242
Alicent High tower.

347
00:28:30.326 --> 00:28:33.829
A true queen counts
the cost to her people.

348
00:28:35.039 --> 00:28:38.626
And yet you toil still
in service to men.

349
00:28:38.709 --> 00:28:41.629
Your father.
your husband. your son.

350
00:28:43.506 --> 00:28:45.132
You desire not to be free.

351
00:28:45.216 --> 00:28:48.302
but to make a window
in the wall of your prison.

352
00:28:49.220 --> 00:28:52.848
Have you never
imagined yourself...

353
00:28:52.932 --> 00:28:55.976
on the Iron Throne?

354
00:28:56.268 --> 00:29:00.106
(Tense music playing)

355
00:29:07.196 --> 00:29:09.073
I'll leave you
with your thoughts.

356
00:29:11.867 --> 00:29:13.786
Ring the bell when
you have an answer.

357
00:29:20.876 --> 00:29:22.711
(Indistinct chatter)

358
00:29:27.466 --> 00:29:30.845
(Ambient street noise)

359
00:29:38.269 --> 00:29:39.562
My Prince.

360
00:29:48.779 --> 00:29:52.783
You yourself are the mysterious
White Worm. I take it.

361
00:29:55.161 --> 00:29:59.039
Or are you simply a further
peel in this stinking onion?

362
00:30:00.958 --> 00:30:03.919
My condolences
on the passing of your king.

363
00:30:05.671 --> 00:30:07.715
[♪ ♪]

364
00:30:19.018 --> 00:30:20.352
Otto:
Where is Prince Aegon?

365
00:30:20.436 --> 00:30:27.109
I thought. the Prince is in Flea
Bottom where no one is to be trusted.

366
00:30:27.193 --> 00:30:29.487
I'd best secrete him
somewhere safe

367
00:30:29.570 --> 00:30:32.323
in case they come
looking for him.

368
00:30:32.406 --> 00:30:34.533
Where's the Prince?

369
00:30:34.617 --> 00:30:37.203
He is safely tucked away.

370
00:30:38.621 --> 00:30:42.166
I want an end
to the savage use

371
00:30:42.249 --> 00:30:44.293
of children in Flea Bottom.

372
00:30:44.376 --> 00:30:47.630
They are forced to fight.
and worse...

373
00:30:47.713 --> 00:30:50.758
your gold cloaks take the
bribes given them to look away.

374
00:30:52.468 --> 00:30:54.803
An obscenity

375
00:30:54.887 --> 00:30:58.891
either tolerated
or ignored by the crown.

376
00:31:00.643 --> 00:31:02.603
I'll look into it.

377
00:31:02.686 --> 00:31:04.313
You have my word.

378
00:31:09.568 --> 00:31:11.320
When your plots ripen

379
00:31:11.403 --> 00:31:14.657
and you install your grandson
on the throne.

380
00:31:14.740 --> 00:31:17.910
remember it was me
who put him there.

381
00:31:17.993 --> 00:31:22.957
I could have killed him
as easily as a wasp on fruit.

382
00:31:23.040 --> 00:31:28.045
There is no power but what
the people allow you to take.

383
00:31:30.714 --> 00:31:31.799
I will remember.

384
00:31:33.384 --> 00:31:38.639
[♪ ♪]

385
00:31:55.864 --> 00:31:58.492
- (Person coughs)
- Listen.

386
00:32:01.954 --> 00:32:03.497
(Coughing)

387
00:32:05.165 --> 00:32:06.709
(Groaning)

388
00:32:06.792 --> 00:32:08.711
No... No!

389
00:32:09.545 --> 00:32:11.589
No! Agh!

390
00:32:13.382 --> 00:32:15.175
(Groans)

391
00:32:15.259 --> 00:32:16.844
(Shouts)

392
00:32:19.221 --> 00:32:21.432
Where is the White Worm?

393
00:32:21.515 --> 00:32:22.683
Erryk:
She sold you for a price.

394
00:32:22.766 --> 00:32:23.892
And why have you paid it?

395
00:32:26.186 --> 00:32:28.731
I want my mother.

396
00:32:28.814 --> 00:32:30.524
Your grandfather. the Hand.

397
00:32:30.608 --> 00:32:32.526
will meet you
outside the city walls.

398
00:32:36.947 --> 00:32:38.032
(Aegon grunting)

399
00:32:40.743 --> 00:32:42.161
You flee what other men
die seeking. Aegon.

400
00:32:42.244 --> 00:32:44.288
(Grunts)

401
00:32:46.707 --> 00:32:48.292
(Grunting)

402
00:32:50.252 --> 00:32:52.087
(Bells tolling)

403
00:32:53.339 --> 00:32:55.591
(Grunts)

404
00:32:55.674 --> 00:32:57.676
[♪ ♪]

405
00:32:59.803 --> 00:33:00.929
I do regret this. friend.

406
00:33:10.773 --> 00:33:13.817
(Swords clang)

407
00:33:17.613 --> 00:33:18.656
(Grunts)

408
00:33:23.077 --> 00:33:25.579
(Intense music playing)

409
00:33:28.916 --> 00:33:29.958
(Grunting)

410
00:33:31.877 --> 00:33:34.546
Prince Aegon: No! Stop! No.

411
00:33:35.047 --> 00:33:37.383
(Aegon giggling)

412
00:33:38.634 --> 00:33:41.887
- I was hoping you disappeared.
- Is our father truly dead?

413
00:33:41.970 --> 00:33:44.264
Yes... and they're
going to make you king.

414
00:33:44.348 --> 00:33:47.059
- (Spits)
- Agh!

415
00:33:47.142 --> 00:33:49.228
- Aegon: No!
- Erryk: Are you going to help me?!

416
00:33:49.311 --> 00:33:51.897
(Grunting)

417
00:33:51.980 --> 00:33:54.441
Aegon: No! Let me go!

418
00:33:54.525 --> 00:33:55.567
Where's your brother. huh?

419
00:33:57.528 --> 00:33:59.238
Let me go!

420
00:33:59.321 --> 00:34:01.699
Brother! Ahh!

421
00:34:07.705 --> 00:34:09.289
Let me go!

422
00:34:09.957 --> 00:34:11.917
I have no wish to rule!

423
00:34:12.000 --> 00:34:14.628
No taste for duty!
I'm not suited.

424
00:34:14.712 --> 00:34:16.213
You'll get no argument from me.

425
00:34:16.296 --> 00:34:20.009
You let me go. I will
find a ship and sail away.

426
00:34:20.092 --> 00:34:21.176
never to be found.

427
00:34:25.180 --> 00:34:26.807
The Queen awaits.

428
00:34:31.687 --> 00:34:35.524
(Tense music playing)

429
00:34:39.361 --> 00:34:42.156
[♪ ♪]

430
00:34:50.038 --> 00:34:51.623
(Door opens)

431
00:34:57.629 --> 00:35:00.758
- Well played.
- None of this is a game.

432
00:35:00.841 --> 00:35:02.968
And yet you treat it as one.

433
00:35:04.303 --> 00:35:05.012
A charming contest.

434
00:35:05.095 --> 00:35:09.892
the... prize.
a pouch of silver.

435
00:35:14.521 --> 00:35:16.690
We have relied on one
another these many years.

436
00:35:16.774 --> 00:35:21.570
And now it is the good of
the family that we both desire.

437
00:35:21.653 --> 00:35:24.907
Whatever our differences.
our hearts remain as one.

438
00:35:26.909 --> 00:35:28.786
Our hearts were never one.

439
00:35:28.869 --> 00:35:30.496
I see that now.

440
00:35:30.579 --> 00:35:32.372
Rather. I have been a piece
that you moved about the board.

441
00:35:32.456 --> 00:35:38.796
If that is true. then I made you
Queen of the Seven Kingdoms.

442
00:35:38.879 --> 00:35:43.008
- Would you have desired it otherwise?
- How could I know?

443
00:35:43.091 --> 00:35:46.094
I wanted whatever you
impressed upon me to want.

444
00:35:47.638 --> 00:35:50.140
And now the debt comes due.

445
00:35:50.224 --> 00:35:53.185
- A debt you were happy enough to pay.
- A sacrifice.

446
00:35:53.268 --> 00:35:58.023
A sacrifice made for
the stability of the realm.

447
00:35:58.107 --> 00:36:00.192
No king has ever lived
that hasn't had to forfeit

448
00:36:00.275 --> 00:36:02.361
the lives of a few
to protect the many.

449
00:36:02.444 --> 00:36:04.655
Though I understand
your squeamishness.

450
00:36:04.738 --> 00:36:08.242
Reluctance to murder
is not a weakness!

451
00:36:11.995 --> 00:36:12.788
I have Aegon.

452
00:36:12.871 --> 00:36:15.499
We'll proceed now as I see fit.

453
00:36:18.460 --> 00:36:20.295
(Alicent sighs)

454
00:36:22.297 --> 00:36:25.425
We will send terms
to Rhaenyra on Dragons tone.

455
00:36:25.509 --> 00:36:28.554
True terms. such that she
may accept without shame.

456
00:36:28.637 --> 00:36:32.391
If she lives. her allies will
mass behind her banners.

457
00:36:32.474 --> 00:36:35.102
- looking for her return.
- Then she must not return.

458
00:36:36.478 --> 00:36:38.063
My husband would have
desired this mercy be shown

459
00:36:38.146 --> 00:36:40.899
- to his daughter.
- Your husband?

460
00:36:40.983 --> 00:36:43.735
Or you. his daughter's
childhood companion?

461
00:36:48.323 --> 00:36:51.368
Criston Cole will be named Lord
Commander of the Kings guard.

462
00:36:52.953 --> 00:36:55.497
My son will be anointed
tomorrow at dawn.

463
00:36:55.581 --> 00:36:59.084
The whole of King's Landing
must witness his ascent.

464
00:36:59.167 --> 00:37:02.796
He will assume authority.
There will be no more dithering.

465
00:37:02.880 --> 00:37:05.299
My son will take the crown of
his namesake. the Conqueror.

466
00:37:05.382 --> 00:37:07.467
and carry Blackfyre.
his sword.

467
00:37:07.551 --> 00:37:11.013
Let the people remember the
ancient strength of House Targaryen.

468
00:37:15.100 --> 00:37:18.103
You look so much like
your mother in certain lights.

469
00:37:24.276 --> 00:37:25.819
(Door opens)

470
00:37:27.112 --> 00:37:30.532
- (Door closes)
- As you wish.

471
00:37:42.502 --> 00:37:44.338
Larys: Your Grace.

472
00:37:46.965 --> 00:37:51.345
The hour is late. Lord Larys.

473
00:37:51.428 --> 00:37:54.348
I've found out something
that you should know.

474
00:38:06.068 --> 00:38:10.238
Have you asked yourself.
I wonder...

475
00:38:10.322 --> 00:38:12.616
how it is... (grunts)

476
00:38:12.699 --> 00:38:14.368
That your father. the Hand...

477
00:38:15.744 --> 00:38:18.789
found Aegon first?

478
00:38:21.959 --> 00:38:24.044
(Alicent sighs)

479
00:38:51.655 --> 00:38:55.367
There is a web of spies
at work in the Red Keep.

480
00:38:55.450 --> 00:39:00.330
Along its threads travels news
of all our doings.

481
00:39:00.414 --> 00:39:05.877
Your father knows this.
but has left it in place.

482
00:39:05.961 --> 00:39:09.423
More than once. it has proved
advantageous to those willing to...

483
00:39:11.008 --> 00:39:13.301
feed the weaver.

484
00:39:14.803 --> 00:39:16.680
And this weaver watches me?

485
00:39:18.682 --> 00:39:20.726
Um...

486
00:39:40.579 --> 00:39:46.084
One of the little spiders
is your lady-in-waiting.

487
00:39:48.003 --> 00:39:50.881
- Talya?
- There are more like her.

488
00:39:50.964 --> 00:39:53.091
Even I do not know their number.

489
00:39:57.637 --> 00:40:01.933
There is one way
to destroy his advantage.

490
00:40:02.017 --> 00:40:04.978
It must be taken out
at the head.

491
00:40:06.688 --> 00:40:11.651
When the Queen dies.
the bees fly without purpose.

492
00:40:13.361 --> 00:40:16.364
Begging your pardon for the
turn of phrase. Your Grace.

493
00:40:16.448 --> 00:40:17.324
(Sighs)

494
00:40:17.407 --> 00:40:21.661
I assume this task falls
within your expertise.

495
00:40:21.745 --> 00:40:24.790
If you wish it...

496
00:40:25.082 --> 00:40:26.583
it will be done.

497
00:40:28.960 --> 00:40:32.005
[♪ ♪]

498
00:40:56.279 --> 00:40:59.324
(Larys breathing heavily)

499
00:40:59.407 --> 00:41:00.450
[♪ ♪]

500
00:41:45.495 --> 00:41:48.206
Erryk:
Out of my way! (Grunting)

501
00:41:55.505 --> 00:41:56.256
With me. Princess.

502
00:41:56.339 --> 00:41:58.884
I cannot let this
treachery stand.

503
00:42:03.138 --> 00:42:06.183
[♪ ♪]

504
00:42:37.214 --> 00:42:38.298
(Birds cawing)

505
00:42:38.381 --> 00:42:41.551
- Where are we?
- Just south of King's Way.

506
00:42:43.428 --> 00:42:44.554
The Blackwater's this way.

507
00:42:46.723 --> 00:42:48.516
[♪ ♪]

508
00:43:13.625 --> 00:43:16.211
I won't leave Meleys.

509
00:43:16.294 --> 00:43:17.379
- If I could get to the Dragon pit. then...
- No.

510
00:43:17.462 --> 00:43:19.172
They'll expect you there.
Princess.

511
00:43:19.256 --> 00:43:22.133
You won't get
past the gates.

512
00:43:22.550 --> 00:43:24.302
Now come.

513
00:43:24.386 --> 00:43:26.513
You must make for the
riverfront and find a ship.

514
00:43:26.596 --> 00:43:28.348
Before they know you've gone.

515
00:43:28.431 --> 00:43:30.517
Watch Captain: (shouting)
Move it! Go! Go!

516
00:43:30.600 --> 00:43:32.060
- (Horse neighs)
- This way!

517
00:43:32.143 --> 00:43:34.813
Keep moving! That's right.

518
00:43:34.896 --> 00:43:36.189
That's right!

519
00:43:38.066 --> 00:43:39.234
- Onward!
- This way.

520
00:43:39.317 --> 00:43:42.195
Watch Captain:
Halt! Halt!

521
00:43:44.739 --> 00:43:46.658
Keep moving!

522
00:43:46.741 --> 00:43:48.576
(Indistinct yelling)

523
00:43:51.454 --> 00:43:54.124
All of you. move forward!

524
00:43:56.710 --> 00:43:59.004
- (Horse neighs)
- Keep moving!

525
00:43:59.087 --> 00:44:01.923
(Indistinct yelling)

526
00:44:04.050 --> 00:44:06.094
(Sheep bleating)

527
00:44:11.224 --> 00:44:13.810
Erryk:
Out of the way!

528
00:44:13.893 --> 00:44:15.854
Out of the way!

529
00:44:15.937 --> 00:44:18.231
(Bells tolling)

530
00:44:18.315 --> 00:44:20.400
(Indistinct chatter)

531
00:44:26.323 --> 00:44:28.408
(Horses galloping)

532
00:44:30.577 --> 00:44:32.162
Hyah! Hyah!

533
00:44:36.082 --> 00:44:38.710
Alicent: Have the
decency to look grateful.

534
00:44:38.793 --> 00:44:42.339
Do you know what has been
done to give you this day?

535
00:44:45.550 --> 00:44:47.469
In an hour. you will be king.

536
00:44:47.552 --> 00:44:50.388
- And my father never wanted this.
- That's not true.

537
00:44:50.472 --> 00:44:52.557
He had 20 years to name me heir
and never did.

538
00:44:52.640 --> 00:44:55.477
Steadfastly. he upheld
Rhaenyra's claim.

539
00:44:55.560 --> 00:44:58.646
- He changed his mind.
- Oh. (Chuckles)

540
00:45:00.648 --> 00:45:01.274
No...

541
00:45:01.358 --> 00:45:05.278
He could have.
but he never did

542
00:45:05.362 --> 00:45:06.780
because he didn't like me.

543
00:45:08.281 --> 00:45:10.533
And yet. with his final breath.

544
00:45:10.617 --> 00:45:13.137
he whispered to me that you
should take his place on the throne.

545
00:45:15.622 --> 00:45:17.207
(Chuckling)

546
00:45:34.015 --> 00:45:37.310
- Do not toy with me. Mother.
- I speak the truth.

547
00:45:44.609 --> 00:45:45.694
(Distant chatter)

548
00:45:51.950 --> 00:45:54.244
Listen to me. Aegon.

549
00:45:54.327 --> 00:45:55.620
Your grandfather. the Hand.
will try to impress on you

550
00:45:55.703 --> 00:45:58.415
that Rhaenyra should be
put to the sword.

551
00:45:58.498 --> 00:46:01.626
You must reject this counsel.

552
00:46:01.709 --> 00:46:03.586
We must not rule with
cruelty and callousness.

553
00:46:03.670 --> 00:46:05.505
For all her faults.
she is your sister.

554
00:46:05.588 --> 00:46:08.091
- your. your father's daughter...
- Do you love me?

555
00:46:10.760 --> 00:46:13.346
- (Bells tolling)
- You imbecile.

556
00:46:13.430 --> 00:46:16.015
Watch Captain: (shouting)
Make way for the royal wheelhouse!

557
00:46:17.684 --> 00:46:20.728
(Indistinct yelling)

558
00:46:27.068 --> 00:46:28.528
(Bells tolling)

559
00:46:32.115 --> 00:46:34.117
Watch Captain: (shouting)
Hey. hey. forward then.

560
00:46:35.785 --> 00:46:38.246
Guard:
Go on. move yourself! Come on!

561
00:46:40.248 --> 00:46:42.041
(Horse neighs)

562
00:46:42.125 --> 00:46:43.960
(Indistinct yelling)

563
00:46:51.259 --> 00:46:54.137
(Captains. guards shouting)

564
00:46:55.930 --> 00:46:57.974
(Bells tolling)

565
00:46:58.057 --> 00:46:59.851
(Bird cawing)

566
00:47:01.436 --> 00:47:03.521
(Indistinct chatter)

567
00:47:07.108 --> 00:47:09.944
(Captains. guards shouting)

568
00:47:12.906 --> 00:47:14.866
(Indistinct chatter)

569
00:47:14.949 --> 00:47:16.784
(Bells tolling)

570
00:47:39.849 --> 00:47:42.393
Otto:
People of King's Landing...

571
00:47:42.477 --> 00:47:45.230
today is the saddest of days.

572
00:47:45.855 --> 00:47:49.067
Our beloved king...

573
00:47:49.150 --> 00:47:51.736
Viserys the Peaceful...

574
00:47:52.195 --> 00:47:54.531
is dead.

575
00:47:55.114 --> 00:47:57.116
(Crowd murmuring)

576
00:47:59.911 --> 00:48:04.374
But it is also the most
joyous of days...

577
00:48:05.458 --> 00:48:08.127
for as his spirit left us...

578
00:48:10.255 --> 00:48:11.631
he whispered his final wish:

579
00:48:11.714 --> 00:48:16.844
That his firstborn son. Aegon...

580
00:48:18.179 --> 00:48:20.473
should succeed him.

581
00:48:20.557 --> 00:48:22.642
(Crowd murmuring)

582
00:48:26.646 --> 00:48:28.356
(Applause)

583
00:48:30.358 --> 00:48:32.694
Commander: Guards!

584
00:48:34.112 --> 00:48:36.447
Out of the way! Move!

585
00:48:44.956 --> 00:48:46.165
Commander: Halt!

586
00:48:46.249 --> 00:48:47.584
Turn!

587
00:48:51.713 --> 00:48:52.797
(Horns blaring)

588
00:48:56.759 --> 00:48:58.803
Commander: Present...

589
00:48:58.886 --> 00:49:01.931
arms!

590
00:49:05.393 --> 00:49:08.229
(Powerful music playing)

591
00:49:12.567 --> 00:49:15.612
[♪ ♪]

592
00:49:33.463 --> 00:49:36.549
Otto: It is your great
good fortune and privilege

593
00:49:36.633 --> 00:49:39.052
to be here to witness this:

594
00:49:41.012 --> 00:49:43.514
A new day for our city...

595
00:49:44.474 --> 00:49:46.517
a new day for our realm.

596
00:49:46.601 --> 00:49:51.773
A new king... to lead us.

597
00:49:51.856 --> 00:49:53.900
[♪ ♪]

598
00:50:37.819 --> 00:50:39.404
(Person coughs)

599
00:50:49.247 --> 00:50:53.000
Septon Eustace: May the
Warrior give him courage.

600
00:50:55.920 --> 00:51:00.425
May the Smith lend strength
to his sword and shield.

601
00:51:02.677 --> 00:51:05.596
May the Father
defend him in his need.

602
00:51:08.057 --> 00:51:12.812
May the Crone
lift her shining lamp

603
00:51:12.895 --> 00:51:16.190
and light his way to wisdom.

604
00:51:16.274 --> 00:51:17.859
(Person coughing)

605
00:51:40.465 --> 00:51:41.966
Criston:
The crown of the Conqueror.

606
00:51:42.049 --> 00:51:44.093
passed down
through generations.

607
00:51:44.177 --> 00:51:46.012
(Aegon breathes deeply)

608
00:52:02.195 --> 00:52:04.614
Let the Seven bear witness:

609
00:52:04.697 --> 00:52:07.492
Aegon Targaryen is the
true heir to the Iron Throne.

610
00:52:07.575 --> 00:52:10.411
(Crowd murmuring)

611
00:52:43.402 --> 00:52:48.115
All hail His Grace.
Aegon.

612
00:52:48.199 --> 00:52:50.034
Second of his Name.

613
00:52:50.117 --> 00:52:53.704
King of the Andals and the
Rhoynar and the First Men.

614
00:52:53.788 --> 00:52:56.123
Lord of the Seven Kingdoms

615
00:52:56.207 --> 00:52:58.876
and Protector of the Realm.

616
00:53:00.962 --> 00:53:03.631
- (Bells tolling)
- Aegon the King!

617
00:53:04.298 --> 00:53:07.552
(Crowd applauds. cheers)

618
00:53:10.721 --> 00:53:12.765
[♪ ♪]

619
00:53:40.376 --> 00:53:41.961
(Cheering)

620
00:53:42.712 --> 00:53:45.756
[♪ ♪]

621
00:54:05.985 --> 00:54:08.154
Crowd: Aegon the
King! Long live Aegon!

622
00:54:13.409 --> 00:54:16.329
- (Crowd screaming)
- (Meleys roars)

623
00:54:19.749 --> 00:54:21.792
(Roaring)

624
00:54:26.881 --> 00:54:28.424
(Screaming)

625
00:54:31.135 --> 00:54:32.720
(Roars)

626
00:54:35.056 --> 00:54:37.141
(Footsteps thudding)

627
00:54:37.224 --> 00:54:38.976
(Screaming)

628
00:54:43.564 --> 00:54:46.400
(Intense music playing)

629
00:54:51.113 --> 00:54:52.657
(Roars)

630
00:55:02.375 --> 00:55:04.919
[♪ ♪]

631
00:55:05.002 --> 00:55:06.837
(Screaming)

632
00:55:10.758 --> 00:55:13.594
Open the doors!

633
00:55:20.810 --> 00:55:22.895
Open the doors!

634
00:55:27.775 --> 00:55:29.462
Get Helaena.

635
00:55:29.777 --> 00:55:31.362
(Roars)

636
00:55:34.824 --> 00:55:37.034
[♪ ♪]

637
00:55:54.218 --> 00:55:56.262
(Screeches)

638
00:56:13.529 --> 00:56:16.323
[♪ ♪]

639
00:56:19.493 --> 00:56:21.078
(Screeches)

640
00:56:25.624 --> 00:56:27.168
(Door closes)

641
00:56:32.048 --> 00:56:35.092
[♪ ♪]

641
00:56:36.305 --> 00:57:36.613
